**Working Capital (September 29 2024)**  

- Total current assets (Table 7): **$25,231 million**  
- Total current liabilities (Table 7): **$10,504 million**  

\[
\text{Working Capital} = \text{Current Assets} - \text{Current Liabilities}
= 25{,}231\ \text{million} - 10{,}504\ \text{million}
= \boxed{14{,}727\ \text{million dollars}}
\]

**Inventory Turnover (2024)**  

\[
\text{Inventory Turnover} = \frac{\text{Cost of Goods Sold (COGS)}}{\text{Average Inventory}}
\]

- **COGS (Cost of revenues, 2024)** = $17,060 million  (Table 8)  
- **Inventories**  
  - 30 Sept 2024 (ending) = $6,423 million (Table 7)  
  - 24 Sept 2023 (beginning) = $6,422 million (Table 7)  

\[
\text{Average Inventory} = \frac{6,423 + 6,422}{2}
                         = \frac{12,845}{2}
                         = 6,422.5\ \text{million}
\]

\[
\text{Inventory Turnover} = \frac{17,060}{6,422.5}
                         \approx 2.66\ \text{times}
\]

**Result:** **≈ 2.66 times** (for the fiscal year ended 30 Sept 2024).

**Average Accounts Receivable**  

\[
\frac{\text{Accounts Receivable}_{2024} + \text{Accounts Receivable}_{2023}}{2}
= \frac{3{,}929\ \text{million} + 3{,}183\ \text{million}}{2}
= \frac{7{,}112\ \text{million}}{2}
= 3{,}556\ \text{million}
\]

**Result:** **$3,556 million**.

**Average Accounts Payable**

\[
\frac{\text{Trade accounts payable (2024)} + \text{Trade accounts payable (2023)}}{2}
= \frac{2{,}584\ \text{million} + 1{,}912\ \text{million}}{2}
= \frac{4{,}496\ \text{million}}{2}
= 2{,}248\ \text{million}
\]

**Result:** **2,248 million** (i.e., $2.248 billion).

**Average Net Fixed Assets**

\[
\frac{\text{Net Fixed Assets (2024)} + \text{Net Fixed Assets (2023)}}{2}
= \frac{4{,}665\ \text{million} + 5{,}042\ \text{million}}{2}
= \frac{9{,}707\ \text{million}}{2}
= 4{,}853.5\ \text{million}
\]

**Result:** **$4,853.5 million**.

**Average Total Assets**  

\[
\frac{\text{Total Assets}_{2024} + \text{Total Assets}_{2023}}{2}
= \frac{55{,}154\ \text{million} + 51{,}040\ \text{million}}{2}
= \frac{106{,}194\ \text{million}}{2}
= 53{,}097\ \text{million}
\]

**Result:** **$53,097 million**.
